## CLI Command Surface

Inside a generated project, prefer `go run manage.go <command>` for
project-aware commands. The generated `manage.go` imports this project and
passes settings, app configs, routes, admin, and queue tasks into Gogo. Use the
installed `gogo` binary for global help/version checks and for creating new
projects.

| Command | Use for |
| --- | --- |
| `gogo help`, `gogo --help`, `gogo -h` | show commands |
| `gogo version`, `gogo --version`, `gogo -version` | show version metadata |
| `gogo startproject [--force] <name> [path]` | create a project scaffold |
| `go run manage.go help`, `go run manage.go --help`, `go run manage.go -h` | show project command help |
| `go run manage.go version`, `go run manage.go --version`, `go run manage.go -version` | show framework version metadata |
| `go run manage.go check` | run settings and system checks |
| `go run manage.go check --deploy` | run production readiness checks |
| `go run manage.go runserver` | run the development HTTP server with project routes and admin mounted |
| `go run manage.go startapp [--force] <name> apps/<name>` | create and auto-install an app scaffold |
| `go run manage.go makemigrations` | create migration files from generated app metadata |
| `go run manage.go migrate` | apply or roll back migrations |
| `go run manage.go showmigrations` | list migration status |
| `go run manage.go sqlmigrate <app> <migration>` | render migration SQL |
| `go run manage.go squashmigrations <app> <start> <end>` | squash migrations |
| `go run manage.go optimizemigration <app> <migration>` | optimize migration operations |
| `go run manage.go createsuperuser` | create an admin user in local CLI auth storage |
| `go run manage.go changepassword` | change a user password in local CLI auth storage |
| `go run manage.go collectstatic` | collect static assets from project and app static roots |
| `go run manage.go shell` | open a project shell |
| `go run manage.go dbshell` | open a database shell |
| `go run manage.go test` | run project tests |
| `go run manage.go worker` | run a queue worker with project task registrations |
| `go run manage.go beat` | run the queue scheduler |
| `go run manage.go inspect` | inspect queue workers and project registered tasks |
| `go run manage.go queues` | inspect queues |
| `go run manage.go dumpdata` | dump fixture data |
| `go run manage.go loaddata` | load fixture data |

Generated project Make commands:

```bash
make test
make check
make run
make tidy
```

## Feature Discovery Workflow For Agents

1. Identify the feature area and route to the matching `.agent/rules/gogo/*`
   rule file.
2. Use the package map above to choose the owning public package.
3. Run `go doc` on the public package or inspect the installed module source
   when exact symbols, options, or examples are needed.
4. Keep app code inside `apps/<app>/` and project wiring inside
   `{{.ProjectName}}/`.
5. Update tests and run focused verification for every behavior change.
6. Do not import internal Gogo packages or copy framework internals into the
   client project.
